03:02:34.800 --> 03:02:36.240
Doing the building

03:02:36.240 --> 03:02:39.760
And doing it in a way that's not completely taken over your life

03:02:39.760 --> 03:02:41.680
Mojito Island is a mirage

03:02:41.680 --> 03:02:42.800
It always was

03:02:42.800 --> 03:02:45.200
There is no retirement for ambitious people

03:02:45.200 --> 03:02:47.120
There is no just sitting back on the beach

03:02:47.120 --> 03:02:49.600
And sipping a mojito for what

03:02:49.600 --> 03:02:50.720
For two weeks

03:02:50.720 --> 03:02:52.560
Before you go damn crazy

03:02:52.560 --> 03:02:54.480
And want to get back into the action

03:02:54.480 --> 03:02:56.320
That's exactly what happens

03:02:56.320 --> 03:02:58.160
To most people who have the capacity

03:02:58.160 --> 03:02:59.920
To build those kinds of exits

03:02:59.920 --> 03:03:01.600
I've never seen

03:03:01.600 --> 03:03:02.640
I shouldn't say never

03:03:02.640 --> 03:03:05.680
I've almost never seen anyone be able to pull that off

03:03:05.680 --> 03:03:07.440
Yet so many think

03:03:07.440 --> 03:03:08.720
That that's why they're doing it

03:03:08.720 --> 03:03:10.720
That's why they're sacrificing everything

03:03:10.720 --> 03:03:13.040
Because once I get to the finish line

03:03:13.040 --> 03:03:13.680
I'm golden

03:03:13.680 --> 03:03:14.400
I've won

03:03:14.400 --> 03:03:15.200
I can retire

03:03:15.200 --> 03:03:16.000
I can sit back

03:03:16.000 --> 03:03:17.280
I can just relax

03:03:17.280 --> 03:03:18.640
And you find out

03:03:18.640 --> 03:03:22.160
That that kind of relaxation is actually hell

03:03:22.160 --> 03:03:22.800
Yeah

03:03:22.800 --> 03:03:24.960
It's hell for creative people

03:03:24.960 --> 03:03:26.720
To squander

03:03:26.720 --> 03:03:30.960
Their god-given creative juices and capacities

03:03:30.960 --> 03:03:32.000
And

03:03:32.000 --> 03:03:34.480
I was really lucky to read the book

03:03:34.480 --> 03:03:36.480
Flow by Mihai

03:03:36.480 --> 03:03:38.080
Chik Sen Mihai

03:03:38.080 --> 03:03:38.640
Early on

03:03:38.640 --> 03:03:39.440
Nice

03:03:39.440 --> 03:03:40.640
The pronunciations

03:03:40.640 --> 03:03:41.920
You know what? I had to practice that

03:03:41.920 --> 03:03:43.600
With AI over the last few days

03:03:43.600 --> 03:03:45.120
Because I knew I was going to cite him

03:03:45.120 --> 03:03:46.720
And I butchered his name

03:03:46.720 --> 03:03:47.440
Several times

03:03:47.440 --> 03:03:49.840
So AI taught me how to pronounce that

03:03:49.840 --> 03:03:51.840
At least somewhat correctly

03:03:51.840 --> 03:03:53.200
But his

03:03:53.200 --> 03:03:54.800
Main

03:03:54.800 --> 03:03:56.160
Work over his career

03:03:56.160 --> 03:03:58.480
Was essentially the concept of flow

03:03:58.480 --> 03:04:00.320
That came out

03:04:00.320 --> 03:04:02.720
Of a search for

03:04:02.720 --> 03:04:04.400
Understanding happiness

03:04:04.400 --> 03:04:05.520
Why are some people happy?

03:04:05.520 --> 03:04:06.880
When are they happy?

03:04:06.880 --> 03:04:09.040
And what he learned was quite illuminating

03:04:09.040 --> 03:04:10.720
He learned that people aren't happy

03:04:10.720 --> 03:04:12.080
When they sit on Muhido Island

03:04:12.080 --> 03:04:13.840
They're not happy when they're free of all

03:04:13.840 --> 03:04:15.600
Obligations and responsibilities

03:04:15.600 --> 03:04:16.160
No

03:04:16.160 --> 03:04:17.440
They're happy

03:04:17.440 --> 03:04:18.960
In these moments

03:04:18.960 --> 03:04:21.280
Where they're reaching and stretching

03:04:21.280 --> 03:04:22.720
Their capacities

03:04:22.720 --> 03:04:25.600
Just beyond what they can currently do

03:04:25.600 --> 03:04:26.880
In those moments of flow

03:04:26.880 --> 03:04:29.120
They can forget time and space

03:04:29.120 --> 03:04:31.280
They can sit in front of the keyboard

03:04:31.280 --> 03:04:32.720
Program a hard problem

03:04:32.720 --> 03:04:34.560
Think 20 minutes of past

03:04:34.560 --> 03:04:36.400
And suddenly it's been three hours

03:04:36.400 --> 03:04:38.160
They look back upon those moments

03:04:38.160 --> 03:04:40.160
With the greatest amount of joy

03:04:40.160 --> 03:04:42.320
And that is what peak happiness is

03:04:42.320 --> 03:04:44.400
If you take away the pursuit

03:04:44.400 --> 03:04:46.480
Of those kinds of problems

03:04:46.480 --> 03:04:49.440
If you eliminate all the problems from your plate

03:04:49.440 --> 03:04:51.760
You're going to get depressed

03:04:51.760 --> 03:04:53.600
You're not going to have a good time

03:04:53.600 --> 03:04:55.120
Now there are people who can do that

03:04:55.120 --> 03:04:56.240
But they're not the same kind of people

03:04:56.240 --> 03:04:57.920
Who build these kinds of companies

03:04:57.920 --> 03:05:00.880
So you have to accept the kind of individual you are

03:05:00.880 --> 03:05:03.280
If you are in this path

03:05:03.280 --> 03:05:04.960
Don't bullshit yourself

03:05:04.960 --> 03:05:06.480
Don't bullshit yourself into thinking

03:05:06.480 --> 03:05:08.080
I'm just going to sacrifice everything

03:05:08.080 --> 03:05:11.440
My health, my family, my hobbies, my friends

03:05:11.440 --> 03:05:13.520
But in 10 years I'm going to make it all up

03:05:13.520 --> 03:05:15.040
Because in 10 years I can do it

03:05:15.040 --> 03:05:16.320
It never works out like that

03:05:16.320 --> 03:05:18.560
It doesn't even work out on both ends of it

03:05:18.560 --> 03:05:20.000
It does not work out if you're successful

03:05:20.000 --> 03:05:20.880
And you sell your company

03:05:20.880 --> 03:05:22.880
Because you'll get bored out of your mind

03:05:22.880 --> 03:05:24.320
Up two weeks on retirement

03:05:24.320 --> 03:05:27.200
It doesn't work out if the company is a failure

03:05:27.200 --> 03:05:29.120
And you regret the last 10 years

03:05:29.120 --> 03:05:30.240
Spent for nothing

03:05:30.240 --> 03:05:32.320
It doesn't work out if it all works

03:05:32.320 --> 03:05:33.440
And you stay in the business

03:05:33.440 --> 03:05:35.280
Because it never gets any easier

03:05:35.280 --> 03:05:37.200
So you're going to fail on all metrics

03:05:37.200 --> 03:05:38.800
If you just go

03:05:38.800 --> 03:05:40.480
There's only work on nothing else

03:05:40.480 --> 03:05:42.960
And I didn't want that

03:05:42.960 --> 03:05:45.040
I wanted the happiness of flow

03:05:45.040 --> 03:05:48.960
I understood that insight was true

03:05:48.960 --> 03:05:50.160
But I wanted to do it in a way

03:05:50.160 --> 03:05:53.360
Where I could sustain the journey for 40 or 50 years

03:05:53.360 --> 03:05:55.760
And there's another interesting caveat

03:05:55.760 --> 03:05:57.920
That I've heard you say is that

03:05:57.920 --> 03:05:59.920
If you do X and you sell your company

03:05:59.920 --> 03:06:00.880
And you want to stay in

03:06:00.880 --> 03:06:02.960
And you want to do another company

03:06:02.960 --> 03:06:06.000
That's going to usually not be as fulfilling

03:06:06.000 --> 03:06:06.480
Yes

03:06:06.480 --> 03:06:08.240
Because really your first baby

03:06:08.240 --> 03:06:09.120
Like

03:06:09.120 --> 03:06:11.280
You can't do it again

03:06:11.280 --> 03:06:12.960
Or most people can't do it again

03:06:12.960 --> 03:06:13.760
A

03:06:13.760 --> 03:06:16.240
Because their second idea is not going to be as good as the first one

03:06:16.240 --> 03:06:17.520
It is so rare

03:06:17.520 --> 03:06:19.120
To capture lightning in the bottle

03:06:19.120 --> 03:06:21.120
Like we have for example with Basecamp

03:06:21.120 --> 03:06:22.400
I know this from experience

03:06:22.400 --> 03:06:24.320
Because I've been trying to build a lot of other businesses since

03:06:24.320 --> 03:06:25.920
And some of them have been moderate successes

03:06:25.920 --> 03:06:27.120
Even good successes

03:06:27.120 --> 03:06:29.040
None of them have been Basecamp

03:06:29.040 --> 03:06:31.520
It's really difficult to do that twice

03:06:31.520 --> 03:06:34.080
But founders or arrogant pricks

03:06:34.080 --> 03:06:34.880
Including myself

03:06:34.880 --> 03:06:36.240
And we like to think that

03:06:36.240 --> 03:06:38.080
Do you know what we succeeded in large part

03:06:38.080 --> 03:06:39.280
Because we're just awesome

03:06:39.280 --> 03:06:41.280
Which is so much better than everyone else

03:06:41.280 --> 03:06:42.880
And in some ways that's true

03:06:42.880 --> 03:06:43.920
Some of the time

03:06:43.920 --> 03:06:46.160
But you can also be really good at something

03:06:46.160 --> 03:06:48.160
That matters for a hot moment

03:06:48.160 --> 03:06:50.000
That that door is open

03:06:50.000 --> 03:06:50.800
The door closes

03:06:50.800 --> 03:06:52.080
Now you're still good at the thing

03:06:52.080 --> 03:06:53.600
But it doesn't matter no one cares

03:06:54.640 --> 03:06:55.600
There's that part of it

03:06:55.600 --> 03:06:57.040
And then there's the part of it that

03:06:57.440 --> 03:07:01.120
Going back to experience things for the first time

03:07:01.120 --> 03:07:02.880
Only happens the first time

03:07:02.880 --> 03:07:04.160
You can't do it again

03:07:04.160 --> 03:07:07.120
I don't know if I have it in me

03:07:07.120 --> 03:07:09.280
To go through the bullshit of the early days again

03:07:09.280 --> 03:07:10.960
And I say bullshit in the sense

03:07:10.960 --> 03:07:12.160
Of the most endearing sense

03:07:12.160 --> 03:07:13.520
It's all great to do it

03:07:13.520 --> 03:07:14.560
I know too much

03:07:14.560 --> 03:07:16.720
This is one of the reasons why

03:07:16.720 --> 03:07:17.760
Whenever I'm asked the questions

03:07:17.760 --> 03:07:19.440
If you could tell your younger self

03:07:19.440 --> 03:07:21.680
Something that would really

03:07:21.680 --> 03:07:23.120
What would you say to your younger self

03:07:23.120 --> 03:07:24.720
I would fucking not say a thing

03:07:24.800 --> 03:07:26.720
I would not rob my younger self

03:07:26.720 --> 03:07:28.640
Of all the life experiences

03:07:28.640 --> 03:07:30.080
That have been blessed with

03:07:30.080 --> 03:07:32.080
Due to the ignorance of how the world works

03:07:32.880 --> 03:07:35.440
Building up the wisdom about how the world works

03:07:35.440 --> 03:07:37.680
Is a joy

03:07:38.320 --> 03:07:39.840
And you got to build it one break out of time

03:07:39.840 --> 03:07:41.840
If you just handed all the results

03:07:41.840 --> 03:07:42.560
It's like

03:07:42.560 --> 03:07:43.680
Oh should we watch your movie?

03:07:43.680 --> 03:07:44.880
Here's how it ends

03:07:44.880 --> 03:07:45.680
I don't want to follow

03:07:45.680 --> 03:07:46.720
I'm watching the movie now

03:07:46.720 --> 03:07:48.320
You spoiled it

03:07:48.320 --> 03:07:49.920
I don't want you to spoil

03:07:49.920 --> 03:07:51.280
My business experience

03:07:51.280 --> 03:07:53.600
I don't want to spoil any of my ignorance

03:07:53.600 --> 03:07:54.960
The greatest blessing

03:07:54.960 --> 03:07:56.800
Half the time when you're starting something new is

03:07:56.800 --> 03:07:58.240
A, you don't know how hard it's going to be

03:07:58.960 --> 03:08:00.880
B, you don't know what you don't know

03:08:01.440 --> 03:08:04.000
Like the adventure is to pay off

03:08:04.560 --> 03:08:06.640
The responsibility is to pay off

03:08:06.640 --> 03:08:07.840
This is something Jordan Peterson

03:08:07.840 --> 03:08:10.240
It's really taught me to articulate

03:08:10.240 --> 03:08:13.440
This notion that responsibility is actually key to meaning

03:08:16.560 --> 03:08:17.520
Man's search for meaning

03:08:17.520 --> 03:08:19.680
Victor Frankl talks about this as well

03:08:19.680 --> 03:08:22.480
That we can endure any hardship

03:08:22.480 --> 03:08:23.760
If there's a reason why

03:08:24.480 --> 03:08:26.000
Now he talked about it in truly

03:08:26.800 --> 03:08:28.320
Life altering

03:08:28.320 --> 03:08:29.840
Concentration camp ways

03:08:29.840 --> 03:08:33.120
But you can also apply at a smaller scale with less criticality

03:08:33.840 --> 03:08:35.520
Of even just your daily life

03:08:35.520 --> 03:08:39.120
That all that hardship in building the original business

03:08:39.120 --> 03:08:41.920
That is responsibility you take upon yourself

03:08:42.640 --> 03:08:44.640
The appeal, the reason you take that on you

03:08:44.640 --> 03:08:46.800
Isn't part because you don't know fully what it entails

03:08:46.800 --> 03:08:47.760
If you had known up front

03:08:47.760 --> 03:08:48.720
If I had known up front

03:08:48.720 --> 03:08:50.160
How hard it would be

03:08:50.160 --> 03:08:50.880
How much

03:08:51.840 --> 03:08:53.680
Frustration there'd be along the way

03:08:53.680 --> 03:08:56.640
If you just told me that in a narrative before I got started

03:08:56.640 --> 03:08:57.280
I would have been like

03:08:57.280 --> 03:08:58.080
Eh

03:08:58.080 --> 03:08:59.440
Maybe I should just go get a job

03:09:00.320 --> 03:09:02.160
I mean you just said so many smart things there

03:09:02.160 --> 03:09:03.120
Just to pick one

03:09:04.560 --> 03:09:05.920
It's funny that sometimes

03:09:06.960 --> 03:09:08.400
The advice givers

03:09:08.400 --> 03:09:10.240
The wisdom givers

03:09:10.880 --> 03:09:13.120
Are have gone through all the bullshit

03:09:14.080 --> 03:09:16.960
And so there is a degree to which you want to make the mistake

03:09:16.960 --> 03:09:19.920
So I think I think I would still give the advice of

03:09:20.560 --> 03:09:22.800
You want to have a stretch of your life

03:09:23.360 --> 03:09:24.560
Where you work too hard

03:09:25.680 --> 03:09:27.280
Including it a thing that fails

03:09:27.920 --> 03:09:29.760
I don't think you can learn the lessons

03:09:29.760 --> 03:09:31.120
Why that's a bad idea

03:09:31.120 --> 03:09:32.240
In any other way

03:09:32.240 --> 03:09:33.440
Except by doing it

03:09:34.160 --> 03:09:35.200
There is a degree

03:09:35.200 --> 03:09:36.720
But of course you don't

03:09:36.720 --> 03:09:38.240
I think you should stretch

03:09:38.240 --> 03:09:40.000
Should you have to stretch for a decade

03:09:40.000 --> 03:09:40.640
I'm not so sure

03:09:40.640 --> 03:09:41.760
Yeah the decade thing is

03:09:41.760 --> 03:09:43.200
20s is a special topic

03:09:43.200 --> 03:09:44.800
It's a lot to trade

03:09:44.800 --> 03:09:46.400
You don't get your 20s back

03:09:46.400 --> 03:09:47.280
You don't get your 30s back

03:09:47.280 --> 03:09:48.560
You don't get your 40s back

03:09:48.800 --> 03:09:49.840
Really

03:09:49.840 --> 03:09:51.360
I would have regretted

03:09:51.360 --> 03:09:52.160
Personally

03:09:52.160 --> 03:09:54.800
If I hadn't done the other things I did in my 20s

03:09:54.800 --> 03:09:56.240
If I hadn't had the fun I had

03:09:56.240 --> 03:09:57.600
If I hadn't had the friends I had

03:09:57.600 --> 03:09:59.680
If I hadn't build up the hobbies that I did

03:09:59.680 --> 03:10:01.120
If I hadn't started

03:10:01.120 --> 03:10:03.520
Driving race cars at an early enough age

03:10:03.520 --> 03:10:05.040
To actually get really good at it

03:10:05.040 --> 03:10:07.200
If I had just gone all in on business

03:10:07.920 --> 03:10:10.160
Because I would have gotten the same out in the end

03:10:10.160 --> 03:10:12.880
This is something Derek Sivers really taught me

03:10:12.880 --> 03:10:14.880
Is he has this great essay

03:10:14.880 --> 03:10:16.320
About how

03:10:16.320 --> 03:10:18.000
When he went for a bike ride

03:10:18.080 --> 03:10:20.320
He could go really hard all out

03:10:20.320 --> 03:10:22.640
And he could do the ride I think in

03:10:22.640 --> 03:10:24.400
Whatever 19 minutes

03:10:24.400 --> 03:10:25.840
Why he could enjoy the ride

03:10:25.840 --> 03:10:27.360
Go 5% slower

03:10:27.360 --> 03:10:29.200
Do the ride in 21 minutes

03:10:30.240 --> 03:10:32.640
And realize there's only two minutes apart

03:10:32.640 --> 03:10:34.480
Either I go all in all the time

03:10:34.480 --> 03:10:35.360
There's nothing else

03:10:35.360 --> 03:10:37.680
I'm completely exhausted at the end

03:10:37.680 --> 03:10:40.000
And or I travel the same distance

03:10:40.000 --> 03:10:42.320
And I arrive maybe two minutes later

03:10:42.320 --> 03:10:44.160
But I got to enjoy the scenery

03:10:44.160 --> 03:10:46.320
Listen to the birds smell the flowers

03:10:47.040 --> 03:10:50.240
That journey is also valuable

03:10:50.240 --> 03:10:53.280
Now I say that while accepting

03:10:53.280 --> 03:10:54.560
And celebrating

03:10:54.560 --> 03:10:56.480
That if you want to be the best

03:10:56.480 --> 03:10:58.480
At one thing in the world

03:10:58.480 --> 03:11:00.160
No you have to sacrifice everything

03:11:00.160 --> 03:11:03.280
You have to be obsessed with just that thing

03:11:03.280 --> 03:11:04.480
There is no instant

03:11:04.480 --> 03:11:06.320
Of someone who's the best in the world

03:11:06.320 --> 03:11:07.040
At something

03:11:07.040 --> 03:11:08.720
Who's not completely obsessed

03:11:08.720 --> 03:11:10.640
I didn't need the best at anything

03:11:10.640 --> 03:11:11.920
This was a

03:11:11.920 --> 03:11:14.400
A rare blessing of humility

03:11:14.400 --> 03:11:15.280
I had early on

03:11:15.280 --> 03:11:16.400
It's like you know what

03:11:16.400 --> 03:11:17.680
I am not that smart

03:11:17.680 --> 03:11:18.560
I'm not that good

03:11:18.560 --> 03:11:19.840
I'm not that talented

03:11:19.840 --> 03:11:21.360
I can do interesting things

03:11:21.360 --> 03:11:23.520
By combining different aspects

03:11:23.520 --> 03:11:24.960
And elements that I know

03:11:24.960 --> 03:11:27.040
But I'm not going to be the best at anything

03:11:27.040 --> 03:11:28.880
And that released me

03:11:28.880 --> 03:11:30.080
From this

03:11:30.080 --> 03:11:31.360
Singular obsession

03:11:31.360 --> 03:11:32.080
We're just going

03:11:32.080 --> 03:11:34.000
I'm going to be the best programmer in the world

03:11:34.000 --> 03:11:34.880
And I know I'm not

03:11:34.880 --> 03:11:36.400
I fucking failed at it

03:11:36.400 --> 03:11:39.680
Twice before I even got how conditionals work

03:11:39.680 --> 03:11:40.880
I'm not smart enough

03:11:40.880 --> 03:11:41.840
To be the best at anything

03:11:41.840 --> 03:11:43.280
I'm not dedicated enough

03:11:43.280 --> 03:11:44.320
To do that

03:11:44.320 --> 03:11:45.520
That's a bit of a

03:11:45.520 --> 03:11:46.160
Blessing

03:11:46.160 --> 03:11:47.120
And I think

03:11:47.120 --> 03:11:48.320
As a society

03:11:48.320 --> 03:11:49.600
We have to straddle

03:11:49.600 --> 03:11:51.840
Both celebrating peak excellence

03:11:51.840 --> 03:11:53.440
Which we do all the time

03:11:53.440 --> 03:11:55.760
And celebrating the peak intensity

03:11:56.320 --> 03:11:56.880
Of mission

03:11:56.880 --> 03:11:58.240
It takes to become that

03:11:58.240 --> 03:11:59.520
And then also going like

03:11:59.520 --> 03:12:00.720
You know what

03:12:00.720 --> 03:12:02.480
We don't all need to be

03:12:02.480 --> 03:12:03.280
Michael Jordan

03:12:03.280 --> 03:12:04.560
Is there going to be one of those

03:12:04.560 --> 03:12:05.760
But we should say that there's

03:12:05.760 --> 03:12:06.880
Certain pursuits

03:12:06.880 --> 03:12:10.880
Where a singular obsession is required

03:12:10.880 --> 03:12:12.320
Basketball is one of them

03:12:12.320 --> 03:12:14.320
By the way, probably racing

