I have to come back to you mentioned it earlier

04:06:25.600 --> 04:06:27.120
Your parent

04:06:27.120 --> 04:06:29.040
Can you speak to the impact

04:06:29.040 --> 04:06:30.800
That becoming a father

04:06:30.800 --> 04:06:32.400
Has had in your life

04:06:32.400 --> 04:06:34.640
I think what's funny about fatherhood is that

04:06:34.640 --> 04:06:37.280
For me I wasn't even sure it's something I wanted

04:06:38.560 --> 04:06:41.440
It took meeting the right woman

04:06:42.160 --> 04:06:43.920
And letting her

04:06:43.920 --> 04:06:45.360
Convince me

04:06:45.360 --> 04:06:47.840
That this was the right idea

04:06:47.840 --> 04:06:50.160
Before we even got started

04:06:50.240 --> 04:06:51.600
I didn't have

04:06:51.600 --> 04:06:55.040
Starting my own family on the list of priorities

04:06:55.040 --> 04:06:57.520
In my late 20s or even early 30s

04:06:58.960 --> 04:07:03.680
It was really the impetus of meeting my wife Jamie

04:07:03.680 --> 04:07:05.360
And her telling me

04:07:05.360 --> 04:07:07.200
This is what I want

04:07:07.200 --> 04:07:08.960
I want to have a family

04:07:08.960 --> 04:07:10.080
I want to get married

04:07:10.080 --> 04:07:11.440
I want to have kids

04:07:11.440 --> 04:07:13.200
I want to have three

04:07:13.200 --> 04:07:15.040
And me going

04:07:16.400 --> 04:07:19.040
For a second like whoa whoa whoa

04:07:19.120 --> 04:07:21.120
And then

04:07:21.120 --> 04:07:23.920
All right let's do it

04:07:23.920 --> 04:07:26.160
And I think

04:07:26.160 --> 04:07:28.160
That's the kind of happy accident

04:07:28.160 --> 04:07:31.280
Where some parts of my life have been very driven

04:07:31.280 --> 04:07:33.280
Where I knew exactly what I wanted

04:07:33.280 --> 04:07:34.640
And how to push forward to it

04:07:34.640 --> 04:07:36.240
And what the payoff was going to be

04:07:37.760 --> 04:07:40.240
But when it comes to having a family

04:07:41.040 --> 04:07:44.720
That always felt like a very fuzzy abstract idea

04:07:44.720 --> 04:07:47.520
The chirps someday

04:07:47.520 --> 04:07:48.960
Maybe

04:07:48.960 --> 04:07:50.480
And then it became very concrete

04:07:50.480 --> 04:07:53.600
Because I met a woman who knew what she wanted

04:07:55.200 --> 04:07:58.080
And looking back on it now

04:07:59.280 --> 04:08:00.800
It almost seems

04:08:02.080 --> 04:08:05.520
Crazy like there's just fork in the road of reality

04:08:05.520 --> 04:08:07.360
Where if that hadn't happened

04:08:07.360 --> 04:08:09.040
And I had been sitting here now

04:08:09.920 --> 04:08:11.280
Not being a father

04:08:11.280 --> 04:08:12.560
Not having a family

04:08:13.680 --> 04:08:16.160
The level of regret

04:08:16.160 --> 04:08:17.600
Knowing what I know now

04:08:17.600 --> 04:08:20.160
About the joys of having that family

04:08:21.280 --> 04:08:22.880
Would have been

04:08:22.880 --> 04:08:24.640
existential

04:08:24.640 --> 04:08:26.400
Would have been

04:08:27.440 --> 04:08:28.880
I don't know if they would have been devastating

04:08:28.880 --> 04:08:32.080
I think men have a little bit of a longer window

04:08:32.080 --> 04:08:33.920
To pursue these things

04:08:33.920 --> 04:08:35.120
Than women do

04:08:35.120 --> 04:08:37.440
There are just certain biological facts

04:08:38.400 --> 04:08:39.920
But

04:08:40.080 --> 04:08:42.720
Ending up with the family I have now

04:08:42.720 --> 04:08:44.400
Ending up with my three boys

04:08:44.480 --> 04:08:46.400
Have been

04:08:46.720 --> 04:08:49.200
Just a transformative experience in the sense that

04:08:49.200 --> 04:08:52.400
Here's something that turned out to be the most important thing

04:08:53.520 --> 04:08:55.280
And it was an open secret

04:08:55.280 --> 04:08:56.480
Not even an open secret

04:08:56.480 --> 04:08:58.240
It was an open truth

04:08:58.240 --> 04:08:59.440
Through all of history

04:08:59.440 --> 04:09:01.520
You listen to anyone who's ever had children

04:09:01.520 --> 04:09:04.720
They will all say my children are the most important to me

04:09:04.720 --> 04:09:07.280
Yet somehow that wisdom couldn't sink in

04:09:07.280 --> 04:09:09.520
Until you were in the situation yourself

04:09:09.520 --> 04:09:12.000
I find those truths fascinating

04:09:12.000 --> 04:09:15.200
When you can't actually relay them with words

04:09:16.160 --> 04:09:17.920
I can tell you hey

04:09:17.920 --> 04:09:19.120
Lex

04:09:19.120 --> 04:09:19.920
What are you doing?

04:09:19.920 --> 04:09:20.720
Get a wife

04:09:20.720 --> 04:09:22.560
Make some kids

04:09:22.560 --> 04:09:23.840
Get a move on it

04:09:23.840 --> 04:09:24.960
And these are just words

04:09:24.960 --> 04:09:25.760
They're not

04:09:25.760 --> 04:09:29.200
Communicating the gravity of what it actually feels to go through the experience

04:09:29.200 --> 04:09:31.360
And you can't really learn it

04:09:31.360 --> 04:09:32.800
Without going through it

04:09:32.800 --> 04:09:34.160
Now of course you can be influenced

04:09:34.160 --> 04:09:36.560
Then whatever we can all help contribute

04:09:36.560 --> 04:09:38.800
And little sparks and little seeds

04:09:38.800 --> 04:09:40.480
Can grow in your your mind about it

04:09:40.480 --> 04:09:41.680
But still has to happen

04:09:42.800 --> 04:09:44.000
And

04:09:44.960 --> 04:09:47.280
Now that I am in this situation

04:09:47.280 --> 04:09:50.960
And just the sheer joy on a daily basis

04:09:50.960 --> 04:09:56.000
Where you think your level of life satisfaction is on a scale of one to ten

04:09:56.000 --> 04:09:57.280
Yeah

04:09:57.280 --> 04:10:00.160
And then the satisfaction of seeing your children

04:10:00.160 --> 04:10:01.600
Understand something

04:10:01.600 --> 04:10:03.760
Accomplish something

04:10:03.760 --> 04:10:04.960
Learn something

04:10:04.960 --> 04:10:05.680
Do something

04:10:05.680 --> 04:10:07.040
Just be

04:10:07.040 --> 04:10:08.560
Just goes like oh my god

04:10:08.560 --> 04:10:10.400
The scale doesn't go from one to ten

04:10:10.400 --> 04:10:12.480
It goes from one to a hundred

04:10:12.480 --> 04:10:14.960
And I've been playing down here in the one to ten range

04:10:15.760 --> 04:10:19.360
All this time and there's a one to a hundred

04:10:20.800 --> 04:10:22.960
That has been humbling

04:10:22.960 --> 04:10:24.960
In a way that

04:10:25.680 --> 04:10:27.440
Is impactful in and of itself

04:10:27.440 --> 04:10:29.520
This whole idea that I thought I had a

04:10:30.320 --> 04:10:33.200
Fair understanding of like the boundaries of life

04:10:34.000 --> 04:10:35.040
In my early 30s

04:10:35.040 --> 04:10:36.000
Like what is this about?

04:10:36.000 --> 04:10:39.120
I mean I've been on this earth long enough now here to know something

04:10:39.120 --> 04:10:40.720
And you were saying I don't know

04:10:40.720 --> 04:10:41.840
I did not know

04:10:41.840 --> 04:10:45.360
I did not know that the scale was much much

04:10:45.360 --> 04:10:46.160
Brother

04:10:46.160 --> 04:10:47.920
And I've often talked about

04:10:49.520 --> 04:10:51.120
The joys of having kids

04:10:51.120 --> 04:10:53.840
And just seeing your own DNA

04:10:53.840 --> 04:10:55.360
Which

04:10:55.600 --> 04:10:58.960
Is remarkable to me because literally that's been the pursuit of

04:10:58.960 --> 04:11:00.720
Human since the dawn of time

04:11:00.720 --> 04:11:02.640
I am here today because

04:11:02.640 --> 04:11:05.440
Whenever 30,000 years ago some Neanderthal

04:11:06.320 --> 04:11:08.960
Had the same realization that I should procreate

04:11:08.960 --> 04:11:11.200
And I should continue my bloodline

04:11:11.840 --> 04:11:14.400
And that all amounts to me sitting here

04:11:14.400 --> 04:11:16.400
Here now but

04:11:16.640 --> 04:11:18.800
It didn't become a practical reality

04:11:18.800 --> 04:11:21.600
To me before meeting the right woman

04:11:21.600 --> 04:11:22.960
And I think that that's

04:11:22.960 --> 04:11:24.320
Sometimes

04:11:24.320 --> 04:11:26.400
Not part of the conversation enough

04:11:26.400 --> 04:11:28.800
That there's something broken at the moment

04:11:28.800 --> 04:11:29.600
About how

04:11:30.400 --> 04:11:32.480
People pair up in the Western world

04:11:33.120 --> 04:11:35.040
And it's at the source of why

04:11:35.040 --> 04:11:36.640
We're not having enough children

04:11:36.640 --> 04:11:38.320
Because there's not enough couples

04:11:38.320 --> 04:11:39.840
There's not enough marriage

04:11:39.840 --> 04:11:41.360
There's not a lot of these

04:11:41.360 --> 04:11:43.840
There's not enough of all these traditional values

04:11:43.840 --> 04:11:46.800
That even 50, 60, 70 years ago

04:11:47.520 --> 04:11:49.200
Was just taking for granted

04:11:49.200 --> 04:11:52.160
We're in this grand experiment

04:11:52.160 --> 04:11:55.760
Of what happens if we just remove a bunch of institutions

04:11:55.760 --> 04:11:58.640
What happens if we no longer value marriage

04:11:58.640 --> 04:12:02.320
As something to aspire to

04:12:02.320 --> 04:12:04.320
What happened if parenthood

04:12:04.320 --> 04:12:06.960
Is now seen in some camps

04:12:06.960 --> 04:12:08.960
It's almost something like

04:12:08.960 --> 04:12:11.840
Weird or against your own self-expression

04:12:11.840 --> 04:12:13.520
It's a grand experiment that

04:12:15.600 --> 04:12:17.440
I'm kind of curious how it turns out

04:12:17.440 --> 04:12:19.280
I'd prefer to watch it as a movie

04:12:19.280 --> 04:12:20.320
Like the children of men

04:12:20.320 --> 04:12:21.440
Of like that was a good show

04:12:21.440 --> 04:12:23.600
I kind of wish that was reality

04:12:23.600 --> 04:12:25.600
But we're seeing that reality play out

04:12:25.680 --> 04:12:29.520
While I'm sitting here in a very traditional

04:12:30.320 --> 04:12:32.480
Two-parent loving household

04:12:32.480 --> 04:12:34.160
With three children and going

04:12:35.280 --> 04:12:36.480
Um

04:12:36.480 --> 04:12:38.080
This is now at the top

04:12:38.080 --> 04:12:39.840
I've done a lot of things in my life

04:12:39.840 --> 04:12:41.280
I've

04:12:41.280 --> 04:12:42.080
Built software

04:12:42.080 --> 04:12:42.880
Built companies

04:12:42.880 --> 04:12:43.760
I've raised cars

04:12:43.760 --> 04:12:44.960
I've done all sorts of things

04:12:45.760 --> 04:12:47.440
And I would trade all of it

04:12:47.440 --> 04:12:48.800
In a heartbeat

04:12:48.800 --> 04:12:50.160
For my kids

04:12:50.160 --> 04:12:53.040
That's just a really fascinating human experience

04:12:53.040 --> 04:12:55.280
That the depth of that bond

04:12:56.080 --> 04:12:57.520
Is something

04:12:57.520 --> 04:12:59.520
You can't appreciate before you have it

04:13:00.240 --> 04:13:01.280
But

04:13:01.280 --> 04:13:03.440
I also think there is a role to play

04:13:04.320 --> 04:13:05.760
To talk it up

04:13:05.760 --> 04:13:07.760
Because we're being bombarded

04:13:07.760 --> 04:13:10.160
Concently with reasons

04:13:10.160 --> 04:13:11.120
Why not to

04:13:11.120 --> 04:13:13.120
Oh, it's too expensive

04:13:13.120 --> 04:13:14.240
Um

04:13:14.240 --> 04:13:17.120
Well, you could get divorced and then you might lose half

04:13:17.120 --> 04:13:19.120
There's all these

04:13:19.120 --> 04:13:19.600
Voices

04:13:19.600 --> 04:13:22.400
Concentry articulating the case against marriage

04:13:22.400 --> 04:13:24.720
The case against having children

04:13:26.400 --> 04:13:30.240
That those of us who chosen to do the traditional thing

04:13:30.960 --> 04:13:32.720
To get marriage and to have children

04:13:32.720 --> 04:13:34.240
Have an obligation

04:13:34.240 --> 04:13:36.240
To kind of talk it up a little bit

04:13:36.240 --> 04:13:38.800
Which would have seen ridiculous again

04:13:38.800 --> 04:13:40.560
50 years ago that you have to talk up

04:13:40.560 --> 04:13:42.400
Something so fundamental of that

04:13:42.400 --> 04:13:44.400
But I have become

04:13:45.920 --> 04:13:47.600
Kind of obligated in that sense

04:13:47.600 --> 04:13:48.640
To do just that

04:13:48.640 --> 04:13:49.440
To talk it up

04:13:49.440 --> 04:13:50.240
To say

04:13:50.240 --> 04:13:51.280
Do you know what

04:13:51.280 --> 04:13:53.600
You can look at everything that I've done

04:13:53.600 --> 04:13:55.520
And if you like some of those parts

04:13:55.520 --> 04:13:58.400
Realize that to me in the situation

04:14:00.720 --> 04:14:02.560
The kids, the family, the wife

04:14:02.560 --> 04:14:03.760
Is more important than all of it

04:14:03.760 --> 04:14:05.120
And it sounds like a cliche

04:14:05.120 --> 04:14:07.280
Because you've heard it a thousand times before

04:14:07.280 --> 04:14:08.880
And by becoming a cliche

04:14:09.440 --> 04:14:11.200
Maybe you start believing it's not true

04:14:11.200 --> 04:14:12.800
That it's just something people say

04:14:14.080 --> 04:14:16.080
But it is reality

04:14:16.080 --> 04:14:17.680
I know almost no parents

04:14:17.680 --> 04:14:20.000
That I have personal relationships with

04:14:20.000 --> 04:14:21.520
That don't consider their children

04:14:21.520 --> 04:14:23.520
To be the most important thing in their life

04:14:23.520 --> 04:14:25.360
So there's a lot of interesting things you say

04:14:25.360 --> 04:14:26.960
So one, it does seem to be

04:14:27.840 --> 04:14:28.640
I know a lot of

04:14:30.240 --> 04:14:31.760
Parents

04:14:31.760 --> 04:14:33.040
Perhaps more interestingly

04:14:33.040 --> 04:14:35.440
I know a lot of super successful people

04:14:35.440 --> 04:14:36.240
Who are parents

04:14:37.200 --> 04:14:37.680
Who

04:14:40.000 --> 04:14:41.760
Really love their kids

04:14:41.760 --> 04:14:43.840
And who say that the kids

04:14:43.840 --> 04:14:45.520
Even helped them to be more successful

04:14:46.320 --> 04:14:48.080
Now the interesting thing

04:14:48.080 --> 04:14:49.520
Speaking to what you're saying is

04:14:49.520 --> 04:14:51.760
It does seem for us humans

04:14:52.400 --> 04:14:54.880
It's easy to articulate the negatives

04:14:56.160 --> 04:14:58.160
Because they're sort of concrete, pragmatic

04:14:58.160 --> 04:14:59.280
You know, it costs more

04:14:59.280 --> 04:15:00.320
It takes some time

04:15:00.960 --> 04:15:02.080
You know, they can be

04:15:02.080 --> 04:15:03.600
You know, crying all over the place

04:15:03.600 --> 04:15:04.240
They're

04:15:04.240 --> 04:15:06.640
You know, tiny narcissists running around

04:15:06.640 --> 04:15:07.040
Whatever

04:15:07.040 --> 04:15:07.680
Which is all true

04:15:07.680 --> 04:15:08.240
But yeah

04:15:08.240 --> 04:15:09.040
Puping everywhere

04:15:09.040 --> 04:15:09.600
That kind of stuff

04:15:11.280 --> 04:15:12.480
But to articulate

04:15:13.280 --> 04:15:14.880
The thing you were speaking to

04:15:15.840 --> 04:15:17.040
There's this little creature

04:15:17.040 --> 04:15:18.400
That you love more than anything

04:15:18.400 --> 04:15:19.600
You've ever loved in your life

04:15:20.400 --> 04:15:22.000
It's hard to convert that into words

04:15:22.000 --> 04:15:23.200
You have to really experience it

04:15:23.200 --> 04:15:25.200
But I believe it

04:15:26.160 --> 04:15:27.760
And I want to experience it that

04:15:27.760 --> 04:15:28.720
But I believe it

04:15:28.720 --> 04:15:30.880
Because just from a scientific method

04:15:30.880 --> 04:15:32.080
Have seen a lot of

04:15:32.800 --> 04:15:34.240
People who are not honestly

04:15:34.240 --> 04:15:35.600
Not very capable of love

04:15:36.880 --> 04:15:39.040
Fall completely in love with their kids

04:15:39.040 --> 04:15:39.520
Yes

04:15:39.520 --> 04:15:40.880
Like, you know, very sort of

04:15:41.680 --> 04:15:43.200
Let's just call it what it is

04:15:43.200 --> 04:15:44.960
Engineers that are very like

04:15:45.280 --> 04:15:46.320
Loop up

04:15:46.320 --> 04:15:48.640
Yes, they just fall in love

04:15:48.640 --> 04:15:49.680
And it's like, all right

04:15:50.800 --> 04:15:52.480
People who just like you said

04:15:52.480 --> 04:15:53.520
They don't really want

04:15:54.160 --> 04:15:55.600
They don't really care

04:15:55.600 --> 04:15:57.120
Or don't really think about having kids

04:15:57.120 --> 04:15:58.080
That kind of stuff

04:15:58.080 --> 04:16:00.000
Once they do it changes everything

04:16:00.000 --> 04:16:01.280
So, you know

04:16:01.280 --> 04:16:02.880
But it's hard to convert into words

04:16:03.520 --> 04:16:05.840
One of the reasons I think it's also difficult is

04:16:07.280 --> 04:16:08.560
I mean, I like kids

04:16:08.560 --> 04:16:10.240
Not that actively dislike them

04:16:11.280 --> 04:16:13.760
But when I was around other people's kids

04:16:13.840 --> 04:16:16.000
I didn't have a emotional reaction

04:16:16.000 --> 04:16:17.280
Some women have, right?

04:16:17.280 --> 04:16:17.920
They see a baby

04:16:17.920 --> 04:16:18.880
And they go, oh

04:16:18.880 --> 04:16:21.520
I never had any emotion of that

04:16:21.520 --> 04:16:22.400
I mean, I could appreciate

04:16:22.400 --> 04:16:24.000
I'm glad for you that you have children

04:16:24.000 --> 04:16:25.600
It did not provoke anything in me

04:16:27.040 --> 04:16:28.480
The emotions that are provoked in me

04:16:28.480 --> 04:16:29.680
When I look at my own children

04:16:30.880 --> 04:16:32.320
This doesn't exist in the same universe

04:16:32.320 --> 04:16:33.200
So you don't have something

04:16:33.200 --> 04:16:34.560
You don't have a complete parallel

04:16:34.560 --> 04:16:35.680
Or at least a lot of men

04:16:35.680 --> 04:16:36.960
Or at least me

04:16:36.960 --> 04:16:39.440
I didn't have sort of a framework to put it into

04:16:39.440 --> 04:16:41.600
What would it be like to have my own child

04:16:41.600 --> 04:16:42.800
And then you experience

04:16:42.800 --> 04:16:44.000
And you just, it's like the

04:16:45.600 --> 04:16:47.440
And it happens so quickly too

04:16:47.440 --> 04:16:49.120
This is what I found fascinating

04:16:49.120 --> 04:16:50.480
It happens before

04:16:50.480 --> 04:16:52.960
That little human is even able

04:16:52.960 --> 04:16:55.680
To return any words to you

04:16:55.680 --> 04:16:59.120
That the love you develop to an infant

04:17:00.000 --> 04:17:00.880
It happens quite quickly

04:17:00.880 --> 04:17:02.080
Not necessarily

04:17:02.560 --> 04:17:03.280
Immediately

04:17:03.280 --> 04:17:03.840
I don't know

04:17:03.840 --> 04:17:05.760
Different people have different experiences

04:17:05.760 --> 04:17:08.240
But it took me a little bit

04:17:08.240 --> 04:17:09.680
But then once it hit

04:17:09.680 --> 04:17:10.880
It just hit like

04:17:10.880 --> 04:17:11.680
Cake of a horse

04:17:12.640 --> 04:17:16.800
And I love that it's also just such a universal experience

04:17:17.520 --> 04:17:20.480
That you can be the most successful person in the world

04:17:20.480 --> 04:17:21.920
You can be the poorest person in the world

04:17:21.920 --> 04:17:23.600
You can be somewhere in the middle

04:17:23.600 --> 04:17:26.400
And we share this experience

04:17:26.400 --> 04:17:27.600
That being a parent

04:17:28.480 --> 04:17:29.920
For most of them

04:17:29.920 --> 04:17:31.920
Turns out to be the most important thing in their life

04:17:32.880 --> 04:17:34.400
But it is really nice

04:17:35.200 --> 04:17:37.920
To do that kind of experience with the right partner

04:17:37.920 --> 04:17:40.080
But I think because I'm such an empath

04:17:40.160 --> 04:17:43.120
